name: aminodeoxychorismate lyase
comment: A pyridoxal-phosphate protein. Forms part of the folate biosynthesis pathway. Acts on 4-amino-4-deoxychorismate, the product of EC 2.6.1.85, aminodeoxychorismate synthase, to form p-aminobenzoate.

references.title: p-Aminobenzoate synthesis in Escherichia coli: purification and characterization of PabB as aminodeoxychorismate synthase and enzyme X as aminodeoxychorismate lyase.
references.journal: Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U. S. A. 87 (1990) 9391-5.

references.title: Characterization and sequence of Escherichia coli pabC, the gene encoding aminodeoxychorismate lyase, a pyridoxal phosphate-containing enzyme.
Three-dimensional structure of 4-amino-4-deoxychorismate lyase from Escherichia coli.
